Alcimedon is either some unknown artist or a fieti- tious name. lenta, ‘lithe,' ‘ pliant.’ Cp. 1. 4 n. facili, ‘plastic' (C.) ; lit. ‘moved easily' over the wood. superaddita, ‘overlaid' (K.). hedera, probably after diffusos, ‘ the vine mantles (with its leaves) the clusters spread by the pale ivy‚' so closely are the two intermingled. 40, 41. in medio, ‘in the field‚’ i.e. the vacant central space. Conon was a Samian astronomer, the friend and instructor of Archi- medes. He is mentioned by Catullus, 66. 2, ‘qui stellarum ortus comperit atque obitus‚' etc. The other is supposed to be Eudoxus of Crete, 'who also wrote phaenomena, or weather prognostics, in connexion with the rising or setting of certain constellations.
